{"type":"message","id":"c27271db","parentId":"f749eefd","timestamp":"2026-03-11T18:02:20.751Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user said \"hi\" - a simple greeting. Let me check the context:\n\n1. I should respond in a friendly, helpful way\n2. I should check if there's any relevant context from memory\n3. The user is in a webchat session\n4. The SOUL.md says to be genuinely helpful, skip the \"Great question!\" filler\n\nLet me check if there's any memory to load (MEMORY.md) - this is a main session so I should load it. But first, let me just greet them naturally since this is a simple greeting.\n\nActually, let me follow the instructions - I should read the key files first according to the project context:\n- SOUL.md - already loaded in context\n- USER.md - already loaded in context  \n- memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md - I should check for recent context\n- MEMORY.md - for long-term memory in main sessions\n\nThe date is Thu 2026-03-12, so the daily file would be memory/2026-03-12.md\n\nBut wait, this is just a \"hi\" greeting. Should I really dive into reading files for a simple greeting? Let me think about what SOUL.md says:\n\n\"Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful. Skip the 'Great question!' and 'I'd be happy to help!' — just help.\"\n\n\"Be the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters.\"\n\nFor a simple \"hi\", being concise is appropriate. I don't need to load all the memory files for a greeting. I should just respond naturally and warmly, then they can tell me what they need."},{"type":"text","text":"Hey! How's it going? What can I help you with today?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"minimax-m2.1","usage":{"input":17804,"output":353,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18157,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773252135267}}
