{"type":"message","id":"81398781","parentId":"e259b0c0","timestamp":"2026-03-11T18:20:29.421Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_10b96c599b154f2083553307","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"total 8\ndrwxr-xr-x 1 node node  160 Mar 11 18:19 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 1 node node   96 Mar 11 18:19 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x 1 node node   96 Mar 11 18:19 .clawhub\n-rw-r--r-- 1 node node 1999 Mar 11 18:19 SKILL.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 node node  133 Mar 11 18:19 _meta.json"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9,"aggregated":"total 8\ndrwxr-xr-x 1 node node  160 Mar 11 18:19 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 1 node node   96 Mar 11 18:19 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x 1 node node   96 Mar 11 18:19 .clawhub\n-rw-r--r-- 1 node node 1999 Mar 11 18:19 SKILL.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 node node  133 Mar 11 18:19 _meta.json","cwd":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773253229416}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e227b8b","parentId":"81398781","timestamp":"2026-03-11T18:20:31.738Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"安装成功了！让我查看一下 SKILL.md 文件的内容。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_93732ab0ac79403283d32e16","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/ddg-web-search/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"minimax-m2.1","usage":{"input":29257,"output":55,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29312,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773253229419}}
{"type":"message","id":"bfa166e4","parentId":"3e227b8b","timestamp":"2026-03-11T18:20:31.757Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_93732ab0ac79403283d32e16","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: ddg-search\ndescription: Web search without an API key using DuckDuckGo Lite via web_fetch. Use as a fallback when web_search fails with missing_brave_api_key error, or whenever you need to search the web and no search API is configured. Provides titles, URLs, and snippets for research queries. Zero dependencies — works with just the built-in web_fetch tool.\n---\n\n# DuckDuckGo Search via web_fetch\n\nSearch the web using DuckDuckGo Lite's HTML interface, parsed via `web_fetch`. No API key or package install required.\n\n## How to Search\n\n```\nweb_fetch(url=\"https://lite.duckduckgo.com/lite/?q=QUERY\", extractMode=\"text\", maxChars=8000)\n```\n\n- URL-encode the query — use `+` for spaces\n- Use `extractMode=\"text\"` (not markdown) for clean results\n- Increase `maxChars` for more results\n\n## Region Filtering\n\nAppend `&kl=REGION` for regional results:\n\n- `au-en` — Australia\n- `us-en` — United States\n- `uk-en` — United Kingdom\n- `de-de` — Germany\n- `fr-fr` — France\n\nFull list: https://duckduckgo.com/params\n\n### Example — Australian search\n\n```\nweb_fetch(url=\"https://lite.duckduckgo.com/lite/?q=best+coffee+melbourne&kl=au-en\", extractMode=\"text\", maxChars=8000)\n```\n\n## Reading Results\n\nResults appear as numbered items with title, snippet, and URL. Skip entries marked \"Sponsored link\" (ads) — organic results follow.\n\n## Search-then-Fetch Pattern\n\n1. **Search** — query DDG Lite for a list of results\n2. **Pick** — identify the most relevant URLs\n3. **Fetch** — use `web_fetch` on those URLs to read full content\n\n## Tips\n\n- First 1-2 results may be ads — skip to organic results\n- For exact phrases, wrap in quotes: `q=%22exact+phrase%22`\n- Add specific terms to narrow results (site name, year, location)\n\n## Limitations\n\n- No time/date filtering (DDG Lite doesn't support `&df=` reliably via fetch)\n- Text results only — no images or videos\n- Results sourced from Bing (may differ from Google)\n- Google search does NOT work via web_fetch (captcha blocked)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":12,"aggregated":"---\nname: ddg-search\ndescription: Web search without an API key using DuckDuckGo Lite via web_fetch. Use as a fallback when web_search fails with missing_brave_api_key error, or whenever you need to search the web and no search API is configured. Provides titles, URLs, and snippets for research queries. Zero dependencies — works with just the built-in web_fetch tool.\n---\n\n# DuckDuckGo Search via web_fetch\n\nSearch the web using DuckDuckGo Lite's HTML interface, parsed via `web_fetch`. No API key or package install required.\n\n## How to Search\n\n```\nweb_fetch(url=\"https://lite.duckduckgo.com/lite/?q=QUERY\", extractMode=\"text\", maxChars=8000)\n```\n\n- URL-encode the query — use `+` for spaces\n- Use `extractMode=\"text\"` (not markdown) for clean results\n- Increase `maxChars` for more results\n\n## Region Filtering\n\nAppend `&kl=REGION` for regional results:\n\n- `au-en` — Australia\n- `us-en` — United States\n- `uk-en` — United Kingdom\n- `de-de` — Germany\n- `fr-fr` — France\n\nFull list: https://duckduckgo.com/params\n\n### Example — Australian search\n\n```\nweb_fetch(url=\"https://lite.duckduckgo.com/lite/?q=best+coffee+melbourne&kl=au-en\", extractMode=\"text\", maxChars=8000)\n```\n\n## Reading Results\n\nResults appear as numbered items with title, snippet, and URL. Skip entries marked \"Sponsored link\" (ads) — organic results follow.\n\n## Search-then-Fetch Pattern\n\n1. **Search** — query DDG Lite for a list of results\n2. **Pick** — identify the most relevant URLs\n3. **Fetch** — use `web_fetch` on those URLs to read full content\n\n## Tips\n\n- First 1-2 results may be ads — skip to organic results\n- For exact phrases, wrap in quotes: `q=%22exact+phrase%22`\n- Add specific terms to narrow results (site name, year, location)\n\n## Limitations\n\n- No time/date filtering (DDG Lite doesn't support `&df=` reliably via fetch)\n- Text results only — no images or videos\n- Results sourced from Bing (may differ from Google)\n- Google search does NOT work via web_fetch (captcha blocked)","cwd":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773253231751}}
{"type":"message","id":"7e6f6be2","parentId":"bfa166e4","timestamp":"2026-03-11T18:20:36.003Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户要求安装 Web Search Pro，我用了 ClawHub 搜索，没有找到 exactly \"web-search-pro\" 但找到了多个相关的 web search 技能。我安装了评分最高的 ddg-web-search。\n\n但用户可能更想要一个 \"Pro\" 版本的搜索技能。让我问问用户是否满意这个安装，或者是否需要其他功能。\n\n另外我应该告诉用户这个技能是关于什么的，以及如何触发它使用。"},{"type":"text","text":"**ddg-web-search** 技能安装完成！✅\n\n**技能信息：**\n- **名称：** ddg-web-search\n- **功能：** 使用 DuckDuckGo Lite 进行网络搜索，无需 API Key\n- **触发方式：** 当需要网络搜索且没有配置 API 时自动使用\n- **位置：** `/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/ddg-web-search/`\n\n**特点：**\n- ✅ 无需 API Key\n- ✅ 支持地区过滤（AU、US、UK、DE、FR 等）\n- ✅ 零依赖\n- ⚠️ 无时间过滤\n- ⚠️ 无图片/视频结果\n\n这个是免费版的 DuckDuckGo 搜索。你原本想要的 **\"Web Search Pro\"** 是指需要 Pro API Key 的高级搜索吗？还是想要其他搜索引擎的技能？\n\n另外 ClawHub 上还有 **Brave Search MCP** (Perplexity 集成) 等高级选项，需要配置 API Key。需要我帮你安装一个需要 API Key 的高级搜索技能吗？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"minimax-m2.1","usage":{"input":29801,"output":292,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30093,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773253231754}}
