{"type":"message","id":"cd4024e9","parentId":"dc8bddfa","timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:04:54.590Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering memory preferences**\n\nI need to check for memory storage related to user preferences. If they ask me to remember something, I should definitely search existing memory first to be well-informed. Since this might be a new preference, I can acknowledge it and write to memory if needed. I'll also think about updating the USER or MEMORY documents to reflect this. It seems smart to perform a memory search about reply style preferences now!\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_EeRTBKn2JG5ais36ZirXBAsX","name":"memory_search","arguments":{"query":"reply style preferences how user wants responses AI味 humanizer-zh future response style preference","maxResults":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1597,"output":217,"cacheRead":55808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57622,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773255887372}}
